main event: A civilian reported seeing one unidentified object over Memphis, Tennessee on October 12, 1969.
interesting points: The sighting was reported to the Air Force and an official investigation was requested.
The witness was asked to complete an AF Form 117 to provide more details about the sighting.
The report indicates there was insufficient data to draw a conclusion about the identity of the object.
The witness was asked to provide a sketch or diagram to help illustrate the sighting.
The report contains instructions for the witness on how to indicate the direction, movement, and location of the object using a compass rose diagram.
